    <node id="The pilot, Jorj Helmuth, successfully reaches orbit around Earth on the Mars rocket. His reaction is not one of excitement or curiosity about the view of Earth from space, but rather a sense of resignation as he knows he has two months of idle time ahead of him.&#10;&#10;During this period, Jorj unstraps and interacts with his pet cat, Sappho. The cat, having experienced free fall before, enjoys herself by bounding around the cabin in curves and gyrations. Jorj plays with her using a string, but eventually grows bored and decides to study the wisdom he will discover on Mars.&#10;&#10;Meanwhile, Sappho curls up and goes to sleep in a spot she carefully selected off the floor. Jorj's interactions with his cat are playful and affectionate, providing a brief respite from his more serious studies." />
