    <node id="Opperly's group is a team of scientists from the Institute, including Hindeman, Gregory, Opperly himself, and young Farquar. They are being referred to in a suspicious context as Jorj has been instructed to investigate their activities.&#10;&#10;Morton Opperly's living room is unique because it is well-kept but worn and behind the times compared to modern standards. Instead of using advanced technology, Opperly prefers traditional methods of reading books, writing with pen and ink, and appreciating a Picasso painting that is still faintly radioactive from its past exposure to radiation. The presence of such a painting suggests that Opperly has taken risks for his passions and may have an unconventional approach to science." />
    <node id="1. Opperly is worried about Farquar accepting the invitation because he believes that the Thinkers, the group who wants their help in producing a nuclear rocket, may not just harm Farquar physically but also manipulate or exploit his personal desires and vulnerabilities for their own gain.&#10;&#10;2. When Opperly asks Farquar if there was a girl once, named Miss Arkady, he is referring to Farquar's past relationship with her, which may have ended badly because she left him for a Thinker. Opperly is implying that the Thinkers might use this information as leverage against Farquar or try to manipulate his emotions to control him.&#10;&#10;3. Opperly's concern also stems from his belief that the role of scientists has changed over time, and they are now exposed to more significant risks and temptations than before. Unlike in the past, when a scientist was an academician with a safe and respectable life, Farquar is at risk of being exploited by powerful forces who want to use his scientific expertise for their benefit.&#10;&#10;4. By mentioning Miss Arkady, Opperly is suggesting that the Thinkers might try to manipulate Farquar's personal feelings or use his past relationships against him, possibly to persuade him to change his aims or betray his colleagues. Overall, Opperly is cautioning Farquar about the potential dangers of accepting the invitation and reminding him to be wary of any attempts to exploit his vulnerabilities or manipulate his emotions." />
