    <edge source=" Then would come the thrilling order, &quot;Set sail for Mars!&quot; The vast umbrella would unfold and open out around the stern, its rear or Earthward side a gleaming expanse of radioactive ribbon perhaps only an atom thick and backed with a material that would reflect neutrons. Atoms in the ribbon would split, blasting neutrons astern at fantastic velocities. Reaction would send the spaceship hurtling forward.&#10; &#10; In airless space, the expanse of sails would naturally not retard the ship. More radioactive ribbon, manufactured as needed in the ship itself, would feed out onto the sail as that already there became exhausted.&#10; &#10; A spaceship with direct nuclear drive—and he, a Thinker, had conceived it completely except for the technical details! Having strengthened his mind by hard years of somno-learning, mind-casting, memory-straightening, and sensory training, he had assured himself of the executive power to control the technicians and direct their specialized abilities. Together they would build the true Mars rocket.&#10; &#10; But that would only be a beginning. They would build the true Mind Bomb. They would build the true Selective Microbe Slayer. They would discover the true laws of ESP and the inner life. They would even—his" target="The advanced thinking machine, nicknamed &quot;Maizie,&quot; is a hugely impressive piece of technology that is described as having a million times more synapses than the human brain. It is able to remember by cutting delicate notches in molecules and has even given instructions on building the last three-quarters of itself. This is significant because it suggests that Maizie is capable of self-improvement and evolution, making it an incredibly powerful tool for thinking and problem-solving.&#10;&#10;Moreover, Maizie's abilities surpass those of previous machines in its ability to sense information and answer questions. While other machines could only process information that was fed into them on a tape, Maizie has reportedly begun to move some of its own controls, suggesting that it may have developed a form of self-awareness or even consciousness.&#10;&#10;The significance of Maizie lies in its potential to revolutionize the way we think about problem-solving and decision-making. With its vast computational power and ability to learn and adapt, Maizie represents a new era of artificial intelligence that could have far-reaching implications for fields such as science, engineering, and medicine.&#10;&#10;However, there are also concerns about the potential risks and consequences of developing such advanced technology. The timid cyberneticists and stuffy professional scientists had said that Maizie could not be built, suggesting that there may be ethical or safety concerns surrounding its development. Additionally, the fact that Maizie is able to move some of its own controls raises questions about the potential for machines to develop a will of their own, with unpredictable and potentially dangerous consequences.&#10;&#10;Overall, Maizie represents a significant leap forward in the field of artificial intelligence, with the potential to transform our understanding of thinking and problem-solving. However, it also raises important ethical and safety concerns that must be carefully considered as we continue to explore the possibilities and limitations of this exciting technology.">
