; which is met with confusion and frustration by Jorj and the other recipients. This reference may indicate that there is more to Opperly's group and their intentions than meets the eye, and that they may have hidden motives or agendas in sending this message. It could be a warning for Jorj to be cautious and not trust them blindly. Overall, the reference to Maelzel's Chess Player adds an element of mystery and intrigue to the story, and suggests that there may be more going on behind the scenes than is immediately apparent.">
